#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.54:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.54:0.2"
msgid "5. Dhammikavagga "
msgstr "5. About Dhammika "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.54:0.3"
msgid "54. Dhammikasutta "
msgstr "54. About Dhammika "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.366, sc1
msgctxt "an6.54:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: See my discussion here: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/about-the-monk-called-dhammika/2682/1
msgctxt "an6.54:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā dhammiko jātibhūmiyaṃ āvāsiko hoti sabbaso jātibhūmiyaṃ sattasu āvāsesu. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Dhammika was a resident in all seven monasteries of his native land. "

msgctxt "an6.54:1.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā dhammiko āgantuke bhikkhū akkosati paribhāsati vihiṃsati vitudati roseti vācāya. "
msgstr "There he abused visiting mendicants; he insulted, harmed, attacked, and harassed them. "

#. VAR: na saṇṭhanti → na saṇṭhahanti (bj)
msgctxt "an6.54:1.4"
msgid "Te ca āgantukā bhikkhū āyasmatā dhammikena akkosiyamānā paribhāsiyamānā vihesiyamānā vitudiyamānā rosiyamānā vācāya pakkamanti, na saṇṭhanti, riñcanti āvāsaṃ. "
msgstr "The visiting mendicants who were treated in this way did not stay. They left, abandoning the monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: jātibhūmakānaṃ → jātibhūmikānaṃ (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an6.54:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho jātibhūmakānaṃ upāsakānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the local lay followers thought to themselves, "

msgctxt "an6.54:2.2"
msgid "“mayaṃ kho bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paccupaṭṭhitā cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena. "
msgstr "“We have supplied the mendicant Saṅgha with robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. "

msgctxt "an6.54:2.3"
msgid "Atha ca pana āgantukā bhikkhū pakkamanti, na saṇṭhanti, riñcanti āvāsaṃ. "
msgstr "But the visiting mendicants don’t stay. They leave, abandoning the monastery. "

msgctxt "an6.54:2.4"
msgid "Ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo yena āgantukā bhikkhū pakkamanti, na saṇṭhanti, riñcanti āvāsan”ti? "
msgstr "What is the cause, what is the reason for this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.54:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho jātibhūmakānaṃ upāsakānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the local lay followers thought to themselves, "

msgctxt "an6.54:2.6"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho āyasmā dhammiko āgantuke bhikkhū akkosati paribhāsati vihiṃsati vitudati roseti vācāya. "
msgstr "“This Venerable Dhammika abuses visiting mendicants; he insults, harms, attacks, and harasses them. "

msgctxt "an6.54:2.7"
msgid "Te ca āgantukā bhikkhū āyasmatā dhammikena akkosiyamānā paribhāsiyamānā vihesiyamānā vitudiyamānā rosiyamānā vācāya pakkamanti, na saṇṭhanti, riñcanti āvāsaṃ. "
msgstr "The visiting mendicants who were treated in this way do not stay. They leave, abandoning the monastery. "

msgctxt "an6.54:2.8"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ dhammikaṃ pabbājeyyāmā”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we banish Venerable Dhammika?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.367, sc3
msgctxt "an6.54:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho jātibhūmakā upāsakā yena āyasmā dhammiko tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ dhammikaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then the local lay followers went up to Venerable Dhammika and said to him, "

msgctxt "an6.54:3.2"
msgid "“pakkamatu, bhante, āyasmā dhammiko imamhā āvāsā; "
msgstr "“Sir, please leave this monastery. "

msgctxt "an6.54:3.3"
msgid "alaṃ te idha vāsenā”ti. "
msgstr "You’ve stayed here long enough.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.54:3.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā dhammiko tamhā āvāsā aññaṃ āvāsaṃ agamāsi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Dhammika left and went to another monastery. "

msgctxt "an6.54:3.5"
msgid "Tatrapi sudaṃ āyasmā dhammiko āgantuke bhikkhū akkosati paribhāsati vihiṃsati vitudati roseti vācāya. "
msgstr "There he abused visiting mendicants; he insulted, harmed, attacked, and harassed them. "

